per dies festos probably means ‘ every holiday‚’ as per autum· nos in 11. 14. 15 and per exactos annos in 111. 22. 6. Dies festi are the same as dies feriati and formed part of the dies nefasti, on which no legal business could be conducted. They are marked le in the calendars (meaning perhaps nefastus feriae ublicae) and there were between 60 and 70 such days in the year in orace's time, besides the various ludi, which lasted many days together, especially in autumn. (Solum, Rb'mische Chronologie, p. 103.)
